---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { defaultSiteConfig } from '../utils/seo';
import type { BreadcrumbItem } from '../utils/schema';

const breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbItem[] = [
  { name: 'Home', url: defaultSiteConfig.siteUrl },
  { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: `${defaultSiteConfig.siteUrl}/privacy/` }
];

const lastUpdated = "February 14, 2026";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Eliava Travel. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-site max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-500">Effective Date: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose-custom">
        <p>
          Eliava Travel ("Company," "we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website, purchase services, or otherwise interact with us.
        </p>
        <p>By using our website or services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>A. Information You Provide Directly</h3>
        <p>When you submit a contact form, schedule a consultation, sign an agreement, purchase services, make a payment through Stripe, or communicate with us, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Phone number</li>
          <li>Business name</li>
          <li>Billing information</li>
          <li>Project details</li>
          <li>Any information voluntarily submitted</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>B. Payment Information (Stripe)</h3>
        <p>
          Payments are processed securely through <strong>Stripe, Inc.</strong> We do not store or process full credit card numbers on our servers. Payment data is collected and processed directly by Stripe in accordance with <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stripe's Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>Stripe may collect payment details, IP address, and fraud-prevention data.</p>

        <h3>C. Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <p>When you visit our website, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>IP address</li>
          <li>Browser type</li>
          <li>Device information</li>
          <li>Pages viewed</li>
          <li>Referring URL</li>
          <li>Date and time of access</li>
        </ul>
        <p>This may be collected via cookies, analytics tools, or similar technologies.</p>

        <h2>2. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR â€” EU/UK Users)</h2>
        <p>If you are located in the European Union or United Kingdom, we process your personal data based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Performance of a contract</li>
          <li>Legitimate business interests</li>
          <li>Legal obligations</li>
          <li>Your consent (where required)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You have the right to withdraw consent at any time.</p>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Deliver consulting services</li>
          <li>Process payments</li>
          <li>Send contracts and invoices</li>
          <li>Communicate about projects</li>
          <li>Improve website performance</li>
          <li>Comply with tax and legal obligations</li>
          <li>Prevent fraud</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information.</p>

        <h2>4. California Privacy Rights (CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
        <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request disclosure of personal information collected</li>
          <li>Request deletion of personal information</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
          <li>Know whether your information is sold or shared (we do not sell personal information)</li>
          <li>Non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact: <a href="mailto:kady@eliavatravel.com">kady@eliavatravel.com</a>. We will verify your identity before processing requests.</p>

        <h2>5. Canada Privacy Rights (PIPEDA)</h2>
        <p>For Canadian users: We collect, use, and disclose personal information only for reasonable business purposes and with consent where required. You may request access to or correction of your personal information by contacting us.</p>

        <h2>6. Australia Privacy Rights (APPs)</h2>
        <p>If you are located in Australia: We handle personal information in accordance with the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs). You may request access to, or correction of, your personal information by contacting us.</p>

        <h2>7. Client System Access (Consulting Services)</h2>
        <p>
          As part of our services, we may receive temporary administrative access to client-owned platforms, including but not limited to email systems, Trello, Zapier, TravelJoy, OpenAI/ChatGPT, and payment or invoicing systems. We access such systems solely for the purpose of delivering contracted services. We do not use client data outside the scope of the engagement. Clients are responsible for revoking access upon project completion.
        </p>

        <h2>8. How We Share Information</h2>
        <p>
          We may share information with trusted service providers including Stripe (payment processing), email providers, scheduling tools, document signing platforms, cloud storage providers, and automation platforms. These providers process information under their own privacy policies. We may also disclose information if required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          If you are located outside the United States, your information may be transferred to and processed in the United States. By using our services, you consent to this transfer. For EU/UK users, appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses may apply where required.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill contractual obligations, comply with tax/accounting/legal requirements, and resolve disputes.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement commercially reasonable safeguards to protect personal information. However, no electronic transmission or storage method is 100% secure.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Cookies & Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We may use cookies and similar technologies to analyze traffic, improve website performance, and measure engagement. You may disable cookies via browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are not directed to individuals under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from minors.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Eliava Travel</strong><br>
          Kady Dennis<br>
          Email: <a href="mailto:kady@eliavatravel.com">kady@eliavatravel.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</PageLayout>
